{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YP85mVqP4yq4sG4F8eiF1A","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import java.util.Optional;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\n     6→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Player;\n     7→\n     8→public interface PlayerRepository extends JpaRepository<Player, String> {\n     9→  List<Player> findByPosition(String position);\n    10→  List<Player> findBySalaryBetween(double low, double high);\n    11→  List<Player> findBySalaryGreaterThan(double salary);\n    12→  List<Player> findByTeams_Id(String teamId);\n    13→  List<Player> findByTeamsIsEmpty();\n    14→  List<Player> findByPositionAndName(String position, String name);\n    15→  List<Player> findDistinctByTeams_League_Id(String leagueId);\n    16→  List<Player> findDistinctByTeams_League_Sport(String sport);\n    17→  List<Player> findDistinctByTeams_City(String city);\n    18→  Optional<Player> findFirstByName(String name);\n    19→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"3ae858b1-36b2-4e28-bacf-7955d1902221"}
