{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LJUQFfvoBgay2uaZt3geHL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     6→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     7→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n     9→\n    10→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\n    11→\n    12→@SpringBootTest\n    13→class RequestSmokeTest {\n    14→\n    15→  @Autowired\n    16→  Request request;\n    17→\n    18→  @Test\n    19→  void roundTrip() {\n    20→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L1\",\"Summer Fun\",\"soccer\"));\n    21→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T1\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"L1\");\n    22→    request.createPlayer(\"P1\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100000);\n    23→    request.addPlayer(\"P1\",\"T1\");\n    24→    assertEquals(1, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"T1\").size());\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"e7101552-2caa-42a6-beef-ca40b0f19f62"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MpeTEPLpqREkYpsH9PsRBv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting - there's a file with a comma in the name (`RequestSmokeText,java`). Now let me proceed with the migration. I'll write all the modified files.\n\nStrategy decision: Since Quarkus has a `quarkus-spring-data-jpa` extension that provides Spring Data JPA compatibility, I'll keep the repository interfaces as-is (they'll still extend `JpaRepository`). However, the complex derived query methods like `findDistinctByTeams_League_Id` may not be fully supported by Quarkus's Spring Data JPA compatibility layer. I need to convert those to use `@Query` annotations with JPQL, or use EntityManager-based implementations instead.\n\nActually, let me take a cleaner approach: Convert the repositories to use EntityManager directly, and migrate the controller to JAX-RS with Jakarta REST. This is a proper Quarkus-native migration.\n\nLet me write all the migrated files now:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":565,"cache_read_input_tokens":63897,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":491},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"18ad1e07-5633-4f0f-9715-20e5da0932ae"}
