{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Q3nNTn1GaeoM4twn3tgT1E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team T1 is properly deleted (404). The issue is that after calling DELETE on `/roster/team/T1`, the `getTeamsOfLeague` still returns 1. This is a timing issue. The `removeTeam` endpoint drops all players from the team and then deletes it, but the league still holds a reference to the team in its `@OneToMany` collection. The `getTeamsOfLeague` query goes through `teamRepository.findByLeague_Id` which runs a fresh query.\n\nWait, the problem might be that the team was already removed by a previous test (drop player test). Let me look at the test flow more carefully. The issue is that the smoke tests run sequentially and share state. After the `test_drop_player` function, player P2 was dropped from team T1. Then `test_remove_entities` tries to delete T1 and check that league L1 has 0 teams.\n\nLet me check what the actual response is:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":223,"cache_read_input_tokens":115056,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":223,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":315},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"b3ad24e8-1c53-4ad6-b953-55520a14c749"}
