{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NnBdhSvM14NWts4av4oeG4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now it's empty. The issue might be a timing issue during the test execution - the `removeTeam` call and the subsequent `getTeamsOfLeague` call happen so quickly that the deletion might not be visible yet due to transaction isolation in Quarkus. Let me look at the `removeTeam` implementation more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the `removeTeam` code flow: the `removeTeam` endpoint calls `request.removeTeam(id)` which uses `@Transactional`. The `teamRepository.deleteById(teamId)` deletes the team. But the issue could be that the League entity still has the Team in its `teams` collection (`@OneToMany(cascade=CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy=\"league\")`). \n\nThe `getTeamsOfLeague` uses `teamRepository.findByLeague_Id(leagueId)` which is a direct query, so it should return fresh data. Let me add a small delay in the test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":638,"cache_read_input_tokens":115279,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":638,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":357},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"83749980-f28c-4cb4-a473-ae1f1ea3cb8f"}
