{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01V2koNQP5aL1XZxy2HkjS36","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The container keeps getting cleaned up by the harness. Let me approach this differently - I should investigate the removeTeam issue in the code itself and fix it, then rebuild and test all at once.\n\nThe problem: `removeTeam` calls `teamRepository.deleteById(teamId)`, but when the League has `@OneToMany(cascade=CascadeType.ALL)` on teams, the League's collection still references the team. With Quarkus/Hibernate, when you query with `teamRepository.findByLeague_Id(leagueId)`, the Hibernate session might still cache the team.\n\nThe real fix is to ensure `removeTeam` properly removes the team from the league's collection before deleting. Let me fix the `removeTeam` implementation:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":151,"cache_read_input_tokens":121005,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":151,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":320},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"d9b903d2-ea4c-46f0-a414-252be355c308"}
