{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YQaPbD9E96cTJUfx1eNGq2","type":"tool_result","content":"   166→\n   167→  @Override\n   168→  public void removeTeam(String teamId) {\n   169→    teamRepository.findById(teamId).ifPresent(t -> {\n   170→      List<Player> players = new ArrayList<>(Optional.ofNullable(t.getPlayers()).orElse(List.of()));\n   171→      for (Player p : players) {\n   172→        t.dropPlayer(p);\n   173→      }\n   174→      teamRepository.save(t);\n   175→      teamRepository.deleteById(teamId);\n   176→    });\n   177→  }\n   178→\n   179→  @Override\n   180→  public TeamDetails getTeam(String teamId) {\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"aaddbe75-9e30-46c0-800d-3712722133ca"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Bvi8HKnvGf1C7UMsBsJdR1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue. The `removeTeam` method drops all players and then calls `teamRepository.deleteById(teamId)`. But it doesn't remove the team from its league's teams collection. In Spring Boot, this worked because Spring Boot's `open-in-view` or its transaction management handles the FK cascade. In Quarkus, the team is deleted at the DB level, but the `findByLeague_Id` query might return a stale result from Hibernate's session cache.\n\nLet me fix `removeTeam` to also remove the team from its league:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":900,"cache_read_input_tokens":121156,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":900,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":578},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"b43bd53c-6ab1-4d43-bc73-37101bc9b070"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Bvi8HKnvGf1C7UMsBsJdR1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Euk8Q7HVKS78tRjYdYDyvD","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__roster__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/spring/tutorial/roster/request/RequestBean.java","old_string":"  @Override\n  public void removeTeam(String teamId) {\n    teamRepository.findById(teamId).ifPresent(t -> {\n      List<Player> players = new ArrayList<>(Optional.ofNullable(t.getPlayers()).orElse(List.of()));\n      for (Player p : players) {\n        t.dropPlayer(p);\n      }\n      teamRepository.save(t);\n      teamRepository.deleteById(teamId);\n    });\n  }","new_string":"  @Override\n  public void removeTeam(String teamId) {\n    teamRepository.findById(teamId).ifPresent(t -> {\n      List<Player> players = new ArrayList<>(Optional.ofNullable(t.getPlayers()).orElse(List.of()));\n      for (Player p : players) {\n        t.dropPlayer(p);\n      }\n      // Remove team from league's collection to keep both sides in sync\n      if (t.getLeague() != null && t.getLeague().getTeams() != null) {\n        t.getLeague().getTeams().remove(t);\n      }\n      t.setLeague(null);\n      teamRepository.save(t);\n      teamRepository.deleteById(teamId);\n    });\n  }"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":900,"cache_read_input_tokens":121156,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":900,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":578},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54aa1ac-75bb-4334-9153-448f533619ac","uuid":"9563b47a-1daf-4308-bb7a-91ff94552b0f"}
